{"body": "If a coder has declared that something has a secure password, it's a fair assumption to make that it's going to handle the validation of that password; After all, the essence of Rails is convention over configuration.\r\n\r\n`SecurePassword` is a very simple solution that should help curb a lot of bad password-retention practices (storing plaintext, storing unsalted MD5 hashes) by making it a no brainer.\r\n\r\nIf your app has authentication routines that are complex enough that it's permissible to have a blank password, use something else.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1091317", "created_at": "2011-05-02T23:46:13Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/354#issuecomment-1091317", "updated_at": "2011-05-02T23:46:13Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 354, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/DanCheail", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/674c8e07920ebbb3a9a1b47e8b89f0fb?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4845b84d63ea5fa8df6268b8d1616a8f.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/received_events", "gravatar_id": "674c8e07920ebbb3a9a1b47e8b89f0fb", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "DanCheail", "type": "User", "id": 9546, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DanCheail/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386199bd3543c151012356"}, "id": 1091317, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/354"}
